## Component Styling & Theme Support

### How Component Styling Works

All components use SCSS modules with semantic CSS variables for automatic theme support.

**Key Principles:**

1. **Semantic Variables Only** - Use `var(--color-text)`, not hardcoded colors
2. **No `!important`** - CSS variables inherit naturally
3. **No Manual Theme Logic** - No `@media (prefers-color-scheme)` in component files
4. **Light Theme First** - Default values at `:root`, overrides in media query

### Semantic Variables Available

All components have access to these variables:

```scss
// Text colors
--color-text              // Primary text (black in light, light gray in dark)
--color-text-subtle       // Secondary text (gray-2 in light, gray-5 in dark)
--color-text-muted        // Tertiary text (gray-1 in light, gray-6 in dark)

// Backgrounds
--color-background        // Page background (primary-blue-light in light, #0f1419 in dark)
--color-foreground        // Component background (white in light, #1a1f26 in dark)

// Borders
--color-border            // Primary border (gray-4 in light, gray-7 in dark)
--color-border-subtle     // Secondary border (gray-3 in light, gray-8 in dark)

// Interactive elements
--color-button-primary              // Button background
--color-button-primary-hover        // Button hover
--color-button-primary-active       // Button active/pressed
--color-button-text-on-primary      // Text on dark button background
--color-input-background            // Input field background
--color-input-border                // Input field border
--color-input-border-hover          // Input on hover
--color-input-border-active         // Input on focus
--color-placeholder                 // Placeholder text

// States
--color-disabled-bg                 // Disabled element background
--color-disabled-text               // Disabled element text
--color-checkbox-unchecked          // Checkbox unchecked state
--color-avatar-placeholder          // Avatar placeholder color

// Links
--color-link                        // Link text
--color-link-hover                  // Link on hover
```

See [PATTERNS.md#9-theme-system-pattern](./PATTERNS.md#9-theme-system-pattern) for complete list.

### Example: Styling a Component

```scss
// src/components/form/button/auButton.scss
.button {
  // Always use semantic variables
  background-color: var(--color-button-primary);
  color: var(--color-button-text-on-primary);
  border: none;

  &:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-button-primary-hover);
  }

  &:active {
    background-color: var(--color-button-primary-active);
  }

  &:disabled {
    background-color: var(--color-disabled-bg);
    color: var(--color-disabled-text);
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }
}
```

### Theme Behavior

**Automatic theme switching:**

1. Component uses semantic variables: `background-color: var(--color-button-primary)`
2. Light mode (default): `--color-button-primary: #075eff` (bright blue)
3. Dark mode (OS preference): `--color-button-primary: #5a95ff` (softer blue)
4. No component code changes needed - CSS variables handle it!

**Browser updates colors automatically when:**

- User changes OS theme preference
- User changes browser theme setting
- No page refresh required - instant update

### What NOT to Do

```scss
// ❌ NEVER use hardcoded colors
.button {
  background-color: #075eff;  // WRONG - won't adapt to dark theme
}

// ❌ NEVER use specific color variables
.button {
  background-color: var(--color-primary-blue);  // WRONG - use semantic instead
}

// ❌ NEVER add @media (prefers-color-scheme) in components
// This is handled globally in src/app/styles/variables.scss
.button {
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    background-color: #5a95ff;  // WRONG - don't do this
  }
}

// ❌ NEVER mix hardcoded colors with variables
.button {
  background-color: var(--color-button-primary);
  border: 1px solid #cccccc;  // WRONG - should use var(--color-border)
}
```

